All charges against Jose A Alvarez in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jose A Alvarez is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

For reasons stated on the record,   Court orders case adjourned for Calendar Call in Branch 05.  Calendar call scheduled for December 21, 2018 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jose A Alvarez in court pro-se. Joshua D. Taggatz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.  Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  The court appointed Attorney Michael Plaisted to represent the defendant; counsel to be paid at the rate of $70.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $25.00 per month commencing at the close of the case.  Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment, subject to tax intercept. Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 20, 2018 at 08:30 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact/No Firearms Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Jessica H.  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
